he final goal is indeed to reach a =\r\nstate of mind where one can accept the fruits of all karmas as prasad of Lo=\r\nrd, with an equanimous mind. However, it is not easy. When we receive the f=\r\nruits of some really terrible karmas, our mind gets so twisted and agitated=\r\n that we lose our balance and our judgment gets badly beated. This may resu=\r\nlt in further bad karmas being committed in that agitated/confused state.\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nThus, it IS sometimes useful to push off some really bad impending k=\r\narmas when one is still in a position to do so. If one reaches a calmer sta=\r\nte of mind in that borrowed time, one may be able to handle the bad fruits =\r\nbetter. It is even possible theoretically that one pushes off a really bad =\r\nkarma, makes progress during that borrowed\n time, reaches an equanimous sta=\r\nte of mind, becomes liberated and then faces the karma as a liberated being=\r\n with a totally equanimous mind that does not get agitated.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 2: Prarabda karma is which was already done and san=\r\nchitha and agami are what we going to do.\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: Actually sanc=\r\nhita karmas are also karmas already done. Sanchita means &quot;piled up&quot;. Prarab=\r\ndha karmas are different in the sense that their fructification has already=\r\n begun. The verb &quot;prArabh&quot; means &quot;to begin&quot;. Its noun form &quot;prArambha&quot; mean=\r\ns &quot;beginning&quot; and its gerund noun form &quot;prArabdha&quot; means &quot;the [one that was=\r\n] begun&quot;. Prarabdha karmas are actions for which the process of reaction ha=\r\ns already begun and in the pipeline. Whereas sanchita karmas are piled up k=\r\narmas that have not kicked off their fruits yet. They can be delayed indefi=\r\nnitely. If one becomes liberated while living, one can merge in Cosmic Self=\r\n without experiencing the fruits of sanchita karmas. However, fruits of pra=\r\nrabdha karmas are already in the pipeline and need to be experienced even b=\r\ny a liberated being.\n=C2=A0\nThough fruits of prarabdha karmas are already i=\r\nn the pipeline, even they can actually be delayed or manipulated. Bottomlin=\r\ne is that there are agents of delivery at the physical and subtle level eve=\r\nn for things deep in the pipeline and hence some limited adjustment is poss=\r\nible.\n\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 3:How does nishkam karma works=\r\n? In other words, when a doer detaches himself from an action, where does t=\r\nhe reaction goes?\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: If one identifies with a body-mind co=\r\nmplex and a limited sense of self-identification and pursues its selfish ag=\r\nenda, one keeps accumulating karmas. But, if one has minimal identification=\r\n with a body-mind complex to just sustain it, pursues no agenda and engages=\r\n in whatever action is natural in the situation one is in (but not driven b=\r\ny any conditioning, i.e. agendas or desires or likes/dislikes), then one is=\r\n untouched by karmas performed in that state.\n=C2=A0\nIn the words of Swami =\r\nSivananda of Hrishikesh, &quot;The accumulated and current actions of a Jnani ta=\r\nke shelter in Brahmanda Prakriti&quot;. In other words, Sanchita karmas (piled u=\r\np actions from past that have not yet begun fructifying) and aagami karmas =\r\n(actions being performed right now) of a liberated being take shelted in\n C=\r\nosmic Kinetic Consciousness (Brahmanda Prakriti).\n\n=C2=A0*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nComment 4: If my destiny is to suffer, why should I pray to God? And=\r\n if i am being \npunished for some kind of bad karma from the past, why am i=\r\n not aware of it? It is like getting punishment without knowing your bad de=\r\neds.\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: One need not pray to God.All one needs to do is to=\r\n stop engaging in problematic karmas to add to the pile of such karmas from=\r\n the past. More importantly, one needs to reach a calm and sustainable stat=\r\ne of mind in which that can be maintained even in the middle of a tumultous=\r\n hurricane caused in one&#39;s life due to serious bad karmas from the past. On=\r\nce serious troubles set in or mind focuses on sense objects, material world=\r\n and one&#39;s pleasures and pains, mind tends to lose its balance and judgment=\r\n, starts pursuing its limited selfish agendas and starts performing even mo=\r\nre bad karmas. Thus, praying to God and contemplating various ideals and qu=\r\nalities that God represents can give a shelter to the mind in which it can =\r\nmaintain some calmness, balance and judgment. If that is not the case for o=\r\nne, perhaps one needs to perfect it further.\n=C2=A0\nGod has no agenda to ei=\r\nther punish you or hide the reason. God is an impartial balancer of reactio=\r\nns to all actions. If there is something unreasonable about the reaction yo=\r\nu are getting, it means your action had a similar unreasonableness.\n\n=C2=A0=\r\nLet me turn around your question on being &quot;aware&quot; and ask a simple question=\r\n. When we cause loss or hurt to someone, do we always tell that person why =\r\nwe are doing it? If not, how can we expect someone to tell us before causin=\r\ng loss or hurt to us? If I caused terrible strife to someone pious and pure=\r\n for no reason, then Nature will use someone in future to cause terrible st=\r\nrife to me despite my piety and purity and apparently for no reason.\n=C2=A0=\r\n\nIn fact, what will you achieve by knowing exactly what was the action that=\r\n caused what is happening to you right now? Why is that useful? More useful=\r\n is your conscience (a representation of God in each heart) that tells you =\r\nright from wrong. It constantly gives guidance on which actions will give g=\r\nood reactions *in future*.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 5: Vasana =\r\ncan be for wealth, fame, power, domination (a struggle for power!) etc. Man=\r\ny ripus, many reasons...!\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: Well-said. Though we are disc=\r\nussing karma and karma phala here, the root cause of karma is vasana in chi=\r\nttaakasha. (Chidaakaasha is the space of pure consciousness and chittaakaas=\r\nha is the space of conditioned consciousness that has likes, dislikes, desi=\r\nres, agendas etc.) Vasishtha defined liberation as overcoming vasanas in Yo=\r\nga Vaasishtham and Patanjali defined yoga as &quot;chitta vR^itti nirodhaH yogaH=\r\n&quot; (resisting the working of conditioning is oneness with Cosmic Self) in Yo=\r\nga Sutras. Until we overcome our vasanas, we are bound. Some are dense and =\r\nsome are very subtle. But all of them bind us.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=\r\n=A0\nComment 6:1. As per Shri Vimalananda, you may also offer all the karmas=\r\n as Homa to inner \ndevas or ishta devta? He mentioned that there is lesser =\r\nof suffering if \nyou do that. Who gets the remaining delta suffering?\n=C2=\r\n=A0\nMy Response: Karmaphala for a specific karma is not a function of that =\r\nkarma alone. It is a function of that karma and one&#39;s current state of mind=\r\n. If someone serves spoiled food, one may get an upset stomach for half day=\r\n or diaria for a week. It depends on how strong one is. Similarly, the same=\r\n karmaphala set in motion by the same external agents of delivery (physical=\r\n & subtle) can cause different reaction inside one, depending on one&#39;s curr=\r\nent state of mind.\n=C2=A0\nAn idle mind is devil&#39;s workshop. Our minds keep =\r\nvibrating with various notions and thoughts. A mind vibrating with selfish =\r\ndesires and unnecessary clutter/confusion *amplifies* the negative effects =\r\nof one&#39;s environment (through which fruits of karmas are\n administered).\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nIf one thinks of ishta devata with reverence and contemplates variou=\r\ns ideals and qualities of ishta devata and mind vibrates with saattwik ener=\r\ngy, it absorbs the negative effects of one&#39;s environment better or at least=\r\n does not amplify them.\n=C2=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology &=\r\n Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\n\n=C2=A0\n\n\n=\r\n&gt;________________________________\n&gt; From: Narasimha P.V.R. Rao &lt;pvr108@yaho=\r\no.com&gt;\n&gt;To: Vedic Wisdom &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;Sent: Sunday, Mar=\r\nch 3, 2013 5:26 PM\n&gt;Subject: Karma, Phala, Remedies, Blessings, Curses etc =\r\n(Re: few questions)\n&gt; \n&gt;\n&gt;Namaste friends,\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Ajit&#39;s reply to Digambe=\r\nr ji&#39;s nice questions is thoughtful. I will add my 2 cents.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0The cosmos run=\r\ns based on the fundamental law that each action (karma) gives a reaction/re=\r\nsult (karmaphala) commensurate with it. Shakti is the sum total of all the =\r\nbeings with various agendas engaging in various karmas and experiencing var=\r\nious karmaphalas. Purusha is the witness of it all.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Though each ka=\r\nrma should give karmaphala that is commensurate with it, that requires an *=\r\nagent* to deliver the karmaphala, i.e. another being. So this requires a co=\r\nmplicated balancing act on part of Cosmic Cumulative Kinetic Consciousness =\r\n(i.e. Shakti). There are very complicated rules that decide the *sequencing=\r\n* of karmaphalas and picking of agents for their delivery.\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;At an=\r\ny time, some karmas from one&#39;s past are placed in a &quot;must experience karmap=\r\nhala in this life&quot; pool, some karmas in a &quot;preferably experience karmaphala=\r\n in this life&quot; pool and the rest in the third pool which may not be experie=\r\nnced anytime soon. The way karmas are assigned and ordered in these pools i=\r\ns based on the balancing of karma/karmaphala sequencing of all beings.\n&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt;The assignment and ordering of these pools will constantly undergo chu=\r\nrn as one engages in various new actions and adds them to the pools. Also, =\r\nas new people enter one&#39;s life, possibilities in terms of karmaphala delive=\r\nry agents and sequencing may change and hence the pools may be re-arranged.=\r\n\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;As one engages in remedial measures suc=\r\nh as prayers, fasting, donations etc, one may transform one&#39;s nature, chang=\r\ne one&#39;s vulnerabilities or re-arrange one&#39;s dynamics with other beings (inc=\r\nluding planets, deities etc, who are the subtle agents of delivery of karma=\r\nphala, who operate through other people who act as physical agents of deliv=\r\nery!). The karma pools may be re-arranged as a result. Some undesirable kar=\r\nmas may be downgraded to a lower pool or pushed down in order within the sa=\r\nme pool. Or, some desirable karmas may be upgraded to a higher pool or push=\r\ned up in order within the same pool.\n&gt;=C2=A0When someone curses or blesses =\r\none, with sufficient mental force behind it (this is the key), the same thi=\r\nng can happen. It is all about re-arranging karmas between the karmik pools=\r\n. Every action by one, or even people around one, has the potential to re-a=\r\nrrange one&#39;s karmik pools. A karma about to give karmaphala may be postpone=\r\nd or a karma that was not to give karmaphala anytime soon may be advanced s=\r\nooner.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;However, remember that the remedial measure has to be as in=\r\ntense as the karma that it is trying to manipulate. You can move a small ro=\r\nck with small force, but you need a large force to move a big rock or a hil=\r\nl.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;If there is no negative karma in one&#39;s pool that can give a s=\r\npecific result, nobody can make one experience that result, no matter what =\r\nritual one does. However, even great souls have a lot of negative karmas in=\r\n their optional pool and even evil people have a lot of positive karmas in =\r\ntheir optional pool, and hence powerful remedies, curses and blessings can =\r\noften make some difference.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;This point is well illustrated by the =\r\n&quot;Guru Charitra&quot; story Digamber ji referred in his point (3).\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;If one thinks that one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s =\r\nactions, one is mistakened. God is not like us human beings, who may show f=\r\navoritism towards those who praise them or bribe them. The He-aspect of God=\r\n is a witness to the play of actions and fruits. The She-aspect of God is t=\r\nhe power that impartially and impassionately manages the fine balance and o=\r\nrder within this play of actions and fruits. All beings are equal in Her ey=\r\nes, from the lowest of evil persons to the noblest of saints. She administe=\r\nrs just and balanced delivery of fruits to actions using available agents.\n=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;The karmas we committed in the past are already in the pipeline an=\r\nd will give their results sooner or later. The best we can do with them, wi=\r\nth some effort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The most important thi=\r\nng is to not add more serious bad karmas to the pipeline now. Simply put, s=\r\nelfish actions and actions that cause pain or harm to others are bad karmas=\r\n and selfless actions and actions that cause pleasure or benefit to others =\r\nare good karmas.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;When it comes to manipulating the pre-existing pi=\r\npeline of karmas awaiting karmaphala, through conscious effort and current =\r\naction, yes, it is possible and general guidelines are available in shastra=\r\ns, but we can&#39;t be certain about the specific impact of each action. One th=\r\ning is for sure - remedial measure for overcoming a karma has to be commens=\r\nurate with the karma\n itself.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;You need only small force to push a =\r\ncat out of your way, but need a large force to push an elephant.\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0\n=\r\n&gt;Best regards,\n&gt;Narasimha\n&gt;--------\n&gt;Astrology & Spirituality Resources: ht=\r\ntp://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n&gt;--------\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt;________________________=\r\n________\n&gt;&gt; From: Ajit Krishnan &lt;ajit.krishnan@...&gt;\n&gt;&gt;To: vedic-wisdo=\r\nm@yahoogroups.com \n&gt;&gt;Sent: Tuesday, February 26, 2013 11:29 PM\n&gt;&gt;Subject: R=\r\ne: [vedic-wisdom] few questions\n&gt;&gt; \n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 \n&gt;&gt;Dear=C2=A0Digamber,\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt;When a kingdom had no royal heirs, a special elephant was appointed by =\r\nthe courtiers to randomly pick the next king. Thus, it was possible for a b=\r\neggar to suddenly find himself the king. Whose karma is this?=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;Vasishtha gives two answers: (1) This is the karma of the ministers, king,=\r\n and all the citizens, and (2) This is the karma of the beggar turned king.=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Everything is interrelated. The beggar&#39;s karma made him a king. Th=\r\ne elephant&#39;s karma allowed him to be the one chosen to pick the king. The m=\r\ninister&#39;s karma allowed them to appoint the elephant to pick the king. And =\r\nthe citizens&#39; karma allowed them to live in such a kingdom, and accept the =\r\nresult.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;The sanskrit word &quot;shaapa&quot; means a curse, or promise, or oa=\r\nth. Many of the curses that we see are for the benefit of mankind, and are =\r\nactually blessings. At the end of the day, some people with a certain amoun=\r\nt of purity of speech discharge their tapas shakti through speech.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=\r\nWhen it comes to people and their karmic pipeline, we usually make an assum=\r\nption. We assume that there is a person, and separate from the person are h=\r\nis many karmas. These karmas can &#39;come&#39; to the person from time to time. We=\r\n then want someone to come and remove all the &quot;bad&quot; karmas from our karmic =\r\npipeline.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Vasishtha teaches us that a &#39;person&#39; and &#39;karma&#39; are the =\r\nsame thing. You are your karmas. And you are nothing but your mind-impressi=\r\nons ... your vaasanaas. In other words, your vaasanaas are your karmas.\n&gt;&gt;\n=\r\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;If you can change your vaasanaas, you have changed your karma. Or cour=\r\nse, that is easier said than done.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Any moment when your mind become=\r\ns quiet is a blessing. Any moment when your mind becomes agitated is a curs=\r\ne. As sadhakas, we run after quieting the mind !\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;sasneham,\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 =C2=A0ajit\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;On Tue, Feb 26, 2013 at 8:08 AM, &lt;dgporob@yahoo.c=\r\nom&gt; wrote:\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Dear Narasimha Ji,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 I was pon=\r\ndering over few things we routinely come across as a part of worship and ho=\r\nw it manipulates karma pipe line,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;(1) When someone gives a `curse&#39; or do=\r\nes a prayoga such as `maran&#39; or `uchhatan&#39; what happens to a person who is =\r\nat receiving end, does his bad karma comes forward or is it a new parabdha =\r\nthat is created. I vaguely remember Vimalananda mentioning something about =\r\na Saint&#39;s curse in Aghora trilogy.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;(2) On similar note, what happens whe=\r\nn you get `blessings&#39; say from a saint or elders? We also come across lot o=\r\nf tantric items like Rudraksha, Parad Shivalinga 