ure=\r\ns such as prayers, fasting, donations etc, one may transform one&#39;s nature, =\r\nchange one&#39;s vulnerabilities or re-arrange one&#39;s dynamics with other beings=\r\n (including planets, deities etc, who are the subtle agents of delivery of =\r\nkarmaphala, who operate through other people who act as physical agents of =\r\ndelivery!). The karma pools may be re-arranged as a result. Some undesirabl=\r\ne karmas may be downgraded to a lower pool or pushed down in order within t=\r\nhe same pool. Or, some desirable karmas may be upgraded to a higher pool or=\r\n pushed up in order within the same pool.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;When someon=\r\ne curses or blesses one, with &lt;span style=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;sufficient=\r\n &lt;/span&gt;mental force behind it (this is the key),\n the same thing &lt;span&gt;can=\r\n &lt;/span&gt;happen. It is all about re-arranging karmas between the karmik pool=\r\ns. Every action by one, or even people around one, has the &lt;span style=3D&quot;f=\r\nont-style:italic;&quot;&gt;potential &lt;/span&gt;to re-arrange one&#39;s karmik pools. A kar=\r\nma about to give karmaphala may be postponed or a karma that was not to giv=\r\ne karmaphala anytime soon may be advanced sooner.&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Howe=\r\nver, remember that the remedial measure has to be as intense as the karma t=\r\nhat it is trying to manipulate. You can move a small rock with small force,=\r\n but you need a large force to move a big rock or a hill.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&lt;div&gt;If there is no negative karma in one&#39;s pool that can give a &lt;span st=\r\nyle=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;specific &lt;/span&gt;result, nobody can make one expe=\r\nrience &lt;span style=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;that &lt;/span&gt;result, no matter wha=\r\nt ritual one does. However, even great souls have a lot of negative karmas =\r\nin their optional pool and even evil people\n have a lot of positive karmas =\r\nin their optional pool, and hence powerful remedies, curses and blessings c=\r\nan often make some difference.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This point is wel=\r\nl illustrated by the &quot;Guru Charitra&quot; story Digamber ji referred in his poin=\r\nt (3).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div=\r\n&gt;If one thinks that one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s actions, one is mist=\r\nakened. God is not like us human beings, who may show favoritism towards th=\r\nose who praise them or bribe them. The He-aspect of God is a witness to the=\r\n play of actions and fruits. The She-aspect of God is the power that impart=\r\nially and impassionately manages the fine balance and order within this pla=\r\ny of actions and fruits. All beings are equal in Her eyes, from the lowest =\r\nof evil persons to the noblest of saints. She administers just and balanced=\r\n delivery of fruits to actions using\n available agents.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br=\r\n&gt;&lt;/div&gt;The karmas we committed in the past are already in the pipeline and =\r\nwill give their results sooner or later. The best we can do with them, with=\r\n some effort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The most important thing=\r\n is to not add more serious bad karmas to the pipeline &lt;span style=3D&quot;font-=\r\nstyle:italic;&quot;&gt;n&lt;span&gt;ow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; Simply put, selfish ac=\r\ntions and actions that cause pain or harm to others are bad karmas and self=\r\nless actions and actions that cause pleasure or benefit to others are good =\r\nkarmas.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;When it comes to manipulating the pre-existing pipelin=\r\ne of karmas awaiting karmaphala, through conscious effort and current actio=\r\nn, yes, it is possible and general guidelines are available in shastras, bu=\r\nt we can&#39;t be certain about the specific impact of each action. One thing i=\r\ns for sure - remedial measure for overcoming a karma has to be commensurate=\r\n with the karma\n itself.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;You need only small force to push a c=\r\nat out of your way, but need a large force to push an elephant.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div sty=\r\nle=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13px;background-color:transparent;font-s=\r\ntyle:normal;font-family:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Bes=\r\nt regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology &amp; Spirituality Resourc=\r\nes: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologe=\r\nr.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, =\r\n0, 0);font-size:13px;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;font-fa=\r\nmily:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;bl=\r\nockquote style=3D&quot;border-left:2px solid rgb(16, 16, 255);&quot;&gt;  &lt;div style=3D&quot;=\r\nfont-size:10pt;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;fo=\r\nnt-size:12pt;font-family:&#39;times new roman&#39;, &#39;new york&#39;, times, serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;di=\r\nv dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=3D&quot;Arial&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;\n &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;span =\r\nstyle=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Ajit Krishnan &lt;ajit.krishna=\r\nn@...&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; ved=\r\nic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com &lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/=\r\nspan&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Tuesday, February 26, 2013 11:29 PM&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-we=\r\night:bold;&quot;&gt;Subject:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;