.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Vas=\r\nishtha teaches us that a &#39;person&#39; and &#39;karma&#39; are the same thing. You are y=\r\nour karmas. And you are nothing but your mind-impressions ... your vaasanaa=\r\ns. In other words, your vaasanaas are your karmas.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;d=\r\niv&gt;If you can change your vaasanaas, you have changed your karma. Or course=\r\n, that is easier said than done.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Any moment when y=\r\nour mind becomes quiet is a blessing. Any moment when your mind becomes agi=\r\ntated is a curse. As sadhakas, we run after quieting the mind !&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div=\r\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;sasneham,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; &nbsp=\r\n;ajit&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;yiv256226775gmail_quote&quot;&gt;On Tue, Feb 26=\r\n, 2013 at 8:08 AM,  &lt;span dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;&lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;ma=\r\nilto:dgporob@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;mailto:dgporob@...&quot;=\r\n&gt;dgporob@...&lt;/a&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt; wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote class=3D&quot;yiv2562267=\r\n75gmail_quote&quot; style=3D&quot;border-left:1px #ccc solid;&quot;&gt;\n\nDear Narasimha Ji,&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; I was pondering over few things we routinely=\r\n come across as a part of worship and how it manipulates karma pipe line,&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n(1) When someone gives a `curse&#39; or does a prayoga such as `maran&#39; or `u=\r\nchhatan&#39; what happens to a person who is at receiving end, does his bad kar=\r\nma comes forward or is it a new parabdha that is created. I vaguely remembe=\r\nr Vimalananda mentioning something about a Saint&#39;s curse in Aghora trilogy.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n(2) On similar note, what happens when you get `blessings&#39; say from =\r\na saint or elders